I think the confusion here is caused by the fact, that an admin can still create new users via the API, even if public registration is disabled. That in itself is OK, but in the policies we do not show the "Email confirmation required" and "Admin must approve new users" options unless "Enable public user registration" is active.

As both of these options are off by default, the scenario described here might have occured after enabling public registration plus requiring admin approval and then disabling public registration again. This would lead to users created via the API needing admin approval afterwards, which can be done via the API as well: [Users_ToggleUserApproval](https://docs.btcpayserver.org/API/Greenfield/v1/#operation/Users_ToggleUserApproval)

@lightningcheckout For us to see how to solve this it'd be good to learn more about the use case.

@pavlenex Yes, I think it was erroneously moved from the general store settings to the configuration of individual payment methods, because it has been and still is a setting on the store-level.

Even on the invoice level, the speed policy is only defined once, so it is the same for every payment method. Changing this to be per payment method would be a larger change and I'm not sure if this is even necessary.

So shall this be moved back to the general store settings to reflect its functionality?

